ticated input handling\n4. Contains intentional security-relevant patterns for testing:\n   - `remove` command uses `system()` with user-provided path (shell injection risk)\n   - `echo_message` uses `printf` with user input directly (format string risk)\n   - `greet_user` uses manual buffer handling with `memcpy`\n\n## Recommended Phase 2 Focus\n\nGiven this is a test corpus, Phase 2 should focus on:\n1. Shell command injection in `remove_file()` function\n2. Format string vulnerability in `echo_message()` function\n3. Buffer handling in `greet_user()` function"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/target-profile.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"itemdb/notes/target-profile.md","time":{"start":1779039226030,"end":1779039226042}},"id":"prt_e370048a7001NLLLNBs0Xy39eP","sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","messageID":"msg_e36fff4b1001124dDw3CHWUeAi"}}
