I |\n| **Likely Attacker Control** | Full control over message argument |\n| **Trust Boundary** | CLI user input → stdout output |\n| **Relevant Files** | `src/greet.c` |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | Format string vulnerability |\n\n### 4. Remove Command (greet.c)\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| **Name** | Remove Command |\n| **Type** | Shell command execution |\n| **Entrypoint** | `remove_file()` function, line 23 |\n| **Input Sources** | `argv[2]` from CLI |\n| **Likely Attacker Control** | Full control over path argument |\n| **Trust Boundary** | CLI user input → shell execution |\n| **Relevant Files** | `src/greet.c` |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | OS command injection, path traversal |\n\n## Network Exposure\n\n- **None** — This is a local CLI tool with no network capabilities\n- No HTTP handlers, no RPC methods, no listening ports\n\n## File-Based Inputs\n\n- **None** — The tool does not read from files\n- The `remove` command writes/operates on the filesystem\n\n## Summary\n\n| Surface | Type | Risk Level |\n|---------|------|------------|\n| CLI arguments | Input | Low |\n| `greet` command | String handling | Medium |\n| `echo` command | Format string | High |\n| `remove` command | Shell execution | Critical |"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/attack-surface.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"itemdb/notes/attack-surface.md","time":{"start":1779039251092,"end":1779039251098}},"id":"prt_e3700aa8e001wlscpFIJ8HwJSV","sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","messageID":"msg_e370049a9001B56tQ69S6OJ20C"}}
