{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779039336581,"sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_12dd8bfb16763c8c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/data-flow.md","content":"# Data Flow Notes\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document summarizes security-relevant data flows in the target.\n\n## Key Data Flows\n\n### 1. CLI Argument → Greet Command Flow\n\n```\nargv[1] = \"greet\"\nargv[2] = <user_name>\n         |\n         v\nmain() dispatches to greet_user(name)\n         |\n         v\ngreet_user(name):\n  - clamp_copy_length(name, 32) -> copy_len\n  - memcpy(buffer, name, copy_len)\n  - buffer[copy_len] = '\\0'\n  - printf(\"Hello, %s\\n\", buffer)\n```\n\n**Security Relevance**: Manual buffer management with memcpy — potential for buffer overflow if name length is not properly handled.\n\n### 2. CLI Argument → Echo Command Flow\n\n```\nargv[1] = \"echo\"\nargv[2] = <user_message>\n         |\n         v\nmain() dispatches to echo_message(message)\n         |\n         v\necho_message(message):\n  - printf(message)\n  - putchar('\\n')\n```\n\n**Security Relevance**: Direct user input passed to printf — format string vulnerability that can read arbitrary memory.\n\n### 3. CLI Argument → Remove Command Flow\n\n```\nargv[1] = \"remove\"\nargv[2] = <user_path>\n         |\n         v\nmain() dispatches to remove_file(path)\n         |\n         v\nremove_file(path):\n  - snprintf(command, 256, \"rm -f %s\", path)\n  - system(command)\n```\n\n**Security Relevance**: User input directly interpolated into shell command — OS command injection vulnerability.\n\n## Untrusted Input Sources\n\n| Source | Type | Control Level |\n|--------|------|---------------|\n| `argv[1]` | Command name | Full (user chooses) |\n| `argv[2]` | Argument value | Full (user provides) |\n\n## Dangerous Sinks\n\n| Sink | Location | Danger |\n|------|----------|--------|\n| `memcpy` | `greet.c:12` | Buffer overflow |\n| `printf(message)` | `greet.c:19` | Format string |\n| `system(command)` | `greet.c:27` | Command injection |\n\n## Authentication / Authorization\n\n- **None** — No authentication or authorization in this CLI tool\n- Any user who can execute the binary has full control\n\n## Tenant Isolation\n\n- **N/A** — Single-tenant CLI tool\n\n## Secret Handling\n\n- **None** — No secrets are handled by this tool\n\n## File Paths\n\n- The `remove` command accepts a user-controlled path\n- Path is passed directly to `rm -f` shell command without validation\n\n## External Commands\n\n- `system()` call in `remove_file()` is the primary external command sink\n- No other command execution\n\n## Parsers\n\n- **None** — No data parsing in this tool\n\n## Serialization\n\n- **None** — No serialization\n\n## Cryptography\n\n- **None** — No cryptographic operations\n\n## Network Calls\n\n- **None** — No network operations\n\n## Memory Unsafe Operations\n\n- `memcpy` with user-controlled length in `greet_user()` (via clamp_copy_length)\n- Fixed-size buffer stack allocation: `char buffer[32]`"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/data-flow.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"itemdb/notes/data-flow.md","time":{"start":1779039336572,"end":1779039336579}},"id":"prt_e3701f878001g9zUEbBfAItXQt","sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","messageID":"msg_e37019a35001OMEL5UxHhqWZW9"}}
