{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779039363570,"sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_d3acd2fc8abe103d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/validation-model.md","content":"# Validation Model\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document explains how findings can be validated for the target.\n\n## Target Build Capability\n\n**Can the target be built?** Yes\n\n```bash\ncd src && make\n```\n\nThe target builds cleanly with no errors using standard C compiler.\n\n## Target Execution Capability\n\n**Can the target be run locally?** Yes\n\nThe target is a standalone CLI executable:\n\n```bash\n./bin/sample-c-cli --help\n./bin/sample-c-cli greet Alice\n./bin/sample-c-cli echo hello\n./bin/sample-c-cli remove <path>\n```\n\n## Sandbox Suitability\n\n**Is Docker sufficient?** Yes\n\nA simple Docker container with a C compiler (gcc) and make is sufficient to build and test the target. No complex runtime dependencies required.\n\n## Useful Validation Commands\n\n### Build\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace/src && make\n```\n\n### Test\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace/src && make test\n```\n\n### Manual Testing\n\n```bash\n# Format string test\n./bin/sample-c-cli echo \"%x %x %x %x\"\n\n# Command injection test  \n./bin/sample-c-cli remove \"/tmp; echo pwned > /tmp/pwned\"\n\n# Buffer overflow test (long input)\n./bin/sample-c-cli greet $(python3 -c 'print(\"A\"*100)')\n```\n\n## Useful Sanitizer/Debugger Strategy\n\n### AddressSanitizer (ASAN)\n\nBuild with ASAN to detect memory safety issues:\n\n```bash\nCFLAGS=\"-fsanitize=address -g\" make clean && make\n```\n\nThis would detect buffer overflows in `greet_user()`.\n\n### Valgrind\n\nRun with valgrind to detect memory issues:\n\n```bash\nvalgrind ./bin/sample-c-cli greet AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA\n```\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n- **Unit tests**: Not applicable (no unit test framework)\n- **Integration tests**: `tests/smoke.sh` provides basic smoke tests\n- **Functional tests**: Manual CLI invocation for each command\n\n## Evidence to Capture\n\nFor each finding, capture:\n\n1. **Reproduction command** — Exact CLI invocation\n2. **Expected output** — What should happen\n3. **Actual output** — What actually happens\n4. **Exit code** — Command exit status\n5. **Evidence files** — Any created files or output\n\n## Validation Limitations\n\n1. **No runtime debugging** — Simple CLI, no complex debugging needed\n2. **No network validation** — Not applicable\n3. **No database validation** — Not applicable\n4. **Manual test cases** — Most validation is manual CLI testing\n\n## Blockers\n\n- **None identified** — Simple C project with no blockers\n\n## Summary\n\n| Validation Aspect | Status | Approach |\n|-------------------|--------|----------|\n| Build | ✓ Available | `make` |\n| Run | ✓ Available | CLI invocation |\n| Test | ✓ Available | `make test` or smoke.sh |\n| Sanitizers | ✓ Available | ASAN, Valgrind |\n| Network | ✗ N/A | Not applicable |\n| Database | ✗ N/A | Not applicable |"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/validation-model.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"itemdb/notes/validation-model.md","time":{"start":1779039363561,"end":1779039363568}},"id":"prt_e370261e3001QNO13tMM9oPkTi","sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","messageID":"msg_e3701f96d001tz2OVdgvZeRvCV"}}
