{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779039390607,"sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_0d29619ece71ab9d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/interesting-files.md","content":"# Interesting Files\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document lists files and directories worth reviewing during Phase 2 (hypothesis generation).\n\n## High-Interest Files\n\n### 1. src/greet.c\n\n| Attribute | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **Path** | `src/greet.c` |\n| **Why Interesting** | Contains all three security-sensitive functions: `greet_user`, `echo_message`, `remove_file` |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | Buffer overflow, format string, command injection |\n| **Recommended Follow-up** | Deep analysis of each function |\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `greet_user()` — Buffer handling with memcpy\n- `echo_message()` — Format string vulnerability\n- `remove_file()` — Shell command injection\n\n### 2. src/main.c\n\n| Attribute | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **Path** | `src/main.c` |\n| **Why Interesting** | CLI entrypoint and argument parsing |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | Argument injection, command routing issues |\n| **Recommended Follow-up** | Review argument handling logic |\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `main()` — Command dispatch based on argv\n\n### 3. src/util.c\n\n| Attribute | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **Path** | `src/util.c` |\n| **Why Interesting** | Contains `clamp_copy_length` used in buffer operations |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | Integer overflow, off-by-one |\n| **Recommended Follow-up** | Verify clamp logic is correct |\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `clamp_copy_length()` — Length calculation for buffer copy\n\n## Medium-Interest Files\n\n### 4. include/greet.h\n\n| Attribute | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **Path** | `include/greet.h` |\n| **Why Interesting** | Public API definitions |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | None — header only |\n| **Recommended Follow-up** | Verify API contracts |\n\n### 5. include/util.h\n\n| Attribute | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **Path** | `include/util.h` |\n| **Why Interesting** | Utility function declarations |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | None — header only |\n| **Recommended Follow-up** | Verify API contracts |\n\n## Low-Interest Files\n\n### 6. src/Makefile\n\n| Attribute | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **Path** | `src/Makefile` |\n| **Why Interesting** | Build configuration |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | None — build system |\n| **Recommended Follow-up** | None required |\n\n### 7. tests/smoke.sh\n\n| Attribute | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **Path** | `tests/smoke.sh` |\n| **Why Interesting** | Test script |\n| **Likely Vulnerability Classes** | None — test file |\n| **Recommended Follow-up** | None required |\n\n## Phase 2 Priority Order\n\n1. **src/greet.c** — Primary target with three vulnerable functions\n2. **src/util.c** — Helper function with potential integer issues\n3. **src/main.c** — Entry point and command routing\n4. Headers — Verify API contracts\n\n## Summary\n\n| File | Interest Level | Priority |\n|------|----------------|----------|\n| src/greet.c | High | 1 |\n| src/util.c | High | 2 |\n| src/main.c | High | 3 |\n| include/greet.h | Medium | 4 |\n| include/util.h | Medium | 5 |\n| src/Makefile | Low | — |\n| tests/smoke.sh | Low | — |"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/interesting-files.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"itemdb/notes/interesting-files.md","time":{"start":1779039390601,"end":1779039390606}},"id":"prt_e3702cb83001frdUaVGX1pbDvL","sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","messageID":"msg_e37026338001Hw222NWZpmxF0i"}}
