{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779039409654,"sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_04ba6aedfab6076b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/security-assumptions.md","content":"# Security Assumptions\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document lists assumptions made during reconnaissance, marked by confidence level.\n\n## Confirmed Assumptions\n\n- [confirmed] The target contains C source files.\n- [confirmed] The target is a CLI tool with no network capabilities.\n- [confirmed] The build system uses Make.\n- [confirmed] The target compiles with no errors using `make`.\n\n## Likely Assumptions\n\n- [likely] The target is intentionally designed as a test corpus with security vulnerabilities.\n- [likely] The `remove` command uses `system()` for shell command execution.\n- [likely] The `echo_message` function has a format string vulnerability.\n- [likely] The `greet_user` function has potential buffer handling issues.\n\n## Unknown Assumptions\n\n- [unknown] Whether the project is meant to have vulnerabilities for testing or if they are accidental.\n- [unknown] Whether there are additional hidden test cases or commands.\n\n## Risky Assumptions\n\n- [risky] The `remove_file` function appears to directly interpolate user input into a shell command.\n- [risky] The `echo_message` function passes user input directly to printf.\n- [risky] Buffer size is hardcoded to 32 bytes in `greet_user()` without validation.\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n| Aspect | Assessment | Risk Level |\n|--------|------------|------------|\n| Input validation | None apparent | High |\n| Buffer handling | Manual with fixed size | Medium |\n| Shell execution | Direct system() call | Critical |\n| Format string | Direct printf of user input | High |\n| Authentication | N/A | N/A |\n| Authorization | N/A | N/A |\n\n## Notes\n\nThis appears to be a test corpus with intentional security vulnerabilities for CodeCome workflow testing. The vulnerabilities are straightforward and clearly exploitable:\n\n1. **Command injection** in `remove_file()` — highest severity\n2. **Format string** in `echo_message()` — high severity\n3. **Buffer handling** in `greet_user()` — medium severity\n\nThe assumptions above should be validated through Phase 2 hypothesis generation and Phase 4 validation."},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/pruiz/Develop/mine/CodeCome-e2e-testing/itemdb/notes/security-assumptions.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"itemdb/notes/security-assumptions.md","time":{"start":1779039409634,"end":1779039409652}},"id":"prt_e370315d7001WIHUs02I4ZFg1X","sessionID":"ses_1c900d483ffe3X7x4o8qKel0y4","messageID":"msg_e3702cc6c001yle4Wmc2eUOMtH"}}
